        "header": "1Introduction",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.22570/2605.22570v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Overview of VGenST-Bench.A) Dataset generation.Given input video themes, our multi-agent pipeline jointly synthesizes videos paired with scene graphs, scenarios, and QA sets.B) Task & level design.Videos are organized along a3×2×23\\times 2\\times 2taxonomy overSpatial scale,Perspective, andScene dynamics, with one spatio-temporal task assigned per cell. QA pairs follow a three-level hierarchy: (L1) Visual perception, (L2) Scene understanding, and (L3) Spatio-temporal reasoning.C) Benchmark statistics.VGenST-Bench comprises 1,200 videos and 33K QA pairs spanning 12 task types and 12 QA types.",
                "position": 323
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "header": "2Related Work",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.22570/2605.22570v1/x3.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:Representative videos for the 12 tasks of VGenST-Bench.Each cell of the3×2×23\\times 2\\times 2taxonomy (Spatial scale×\\timesPerspective×\\timesScene dynamics) is paired with one dedicated reasoning task. Rows correspond to spatial scales (Figural / Vista / Environmental); columns are grouped by perspective (Egocentric / Exocentric) and scene dynamics (Static / Dynamic). Each strip shows four sampled frames from a representative video for the task.",
                "position": 470
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "header": "3VGenST-Bench",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.22570/2605.22570v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Table 2:Twelve tasks of VGenST-Bench, organized along the3×2×23\\times 2\\times 2taxonomy (Spatial scale×\\timesPerspective×\\timesScene dynamics). Each cell contains the task code (bold) and full name.",
                "position": 488
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.22570/2605.22570v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:VGenST-Bench construction pipeline.Starting from a theme, four agents operate in sequence. TheScene Graph Agentproduces a structured scene graph specifying objects and spatial composition; theScenario Agentexpands it into a temporally grounded scenario with reasoning goal and timeline; theVideo Agentsynthesizes the corresponding image and video through generative models; and theQA Agentgenerates base MCQs from a task–QA applicability matrix and reformats each into three variants.",
                "position": 670
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "header": "4Experiments",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.22570/2605.22570v1/x5.png",
                "caption": "Figure 6:Robustness Analysis.(a) None-of-these variants show a clear asymmetry: V1 maintains base accuracy, while V2 produces dramatic drops across all models.\n(b) Open-ended evaluation by question level reveals large drop on L3 for all models.\nTogether, these reveal that closed-form MCQ accuracy may overestimate spatio-temporal reasoning capability.",
                "position": 692
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.22570/2605.22570v1/x6.png",
                "caption": "Figure 7:Reasoning failure ofDirection Estimationtask.The model’s reasoning trace correctly identifies the initial orientation, the leftward camera turn, and the final view, but inverts the resulting egocentric direction at the final step, concluding with the wrong answer.",
                "position": 707
            }
        ]
